	"metadata": {
		"inclusion": "To add or include the LTA-ML into a Z-Wave network:\r\nAfter installing LTA-ML near the PiACK II, and then connecting to the AC Adapter which is included in the same package:\r\n1.\tSet the controller in inclusion mode.\r\n2.\tPush the “pairing” button once.\r\n3.\tWait 5 seconds.\r\n4.\tConfirm the “Home Gateway” LED of the front panel is on.\r\n",
		"exclusion": "To remove or exclude the LTA-ML from a Z-Wave network:\r\n1.\tSet the controller in exclusion mode.\r\n2.\tPush the “pairing” button 3 times.\r\n3.\tConfirm the “Home Gateway” LED of the front panel is off.",
		"reset": "To factory reset the LTA-ML:\r\n1.\tConfirm the LTA-ML has been already included into a Z-Wave network.\r\n2.\tRemove the AC adapter’s plug and turn off the LTA-ML.\r\n3.\tSet the AC adapter’s plug again and wait more than 15 seconds but no longer than 75 seconds.\r\n4.\tPush the “pairing” button for 10 seconds and the “Home Gateway” LED turns off.\r\n※Please use this procedure only when the primary controller is missing or otherwise inoperable.\r\n"
